text: Preparation Put out all of the ingredients first. A successful baking experience always begins with having all the ingredients in front of you for easy and quick access. Assemble the things you need to make the brownies with. As well as the ingredients, also put together the cooking tools, as listed below under Things You'll Need. Pre-heat the oven to 350ºF (180ºC).  Prepare the cooking pan. Spray the cooking spray evenly unto the surface of the 8-inch baking pan before putting the mixture in the pan. Making the Brownie Batter Add the ingredients. Place the cake mix, eggs, oil, powdered sugar, and water/milk into the medium to large sized bowl. Combine the ingredients. Mix the ingredients together for 5-7 minutes. Baking the Brownies Transfer the mixture into the prepared pan. Put the pan into the oven. Set a timer for 15 minutes. Bake for 15 minutes or up until the brownies are not gooey anymore. Check every five minutes to make sure the brownies are baking well. Use a fork to check if the brownies need to be baked more. Making the Brownies Take the brownies out of the oven. Leaving them in the pan, let them cool for 5 to 10 minutes. Sprinkle powdered sugar across the brownie slab. This is easiest done before cutting. Cut the brownies into small squares. Make the squares evenly sized. Serve. The brownies are now ready for eating. They can be eaten as a snack or enjoyed as a dessert dish with ice cream as well!
